LStages-micro

A Model with n-Larval Stages for exDE

David Smith

2022-10-28

\(\uparrow\) Library || Aquatic Ecology

For BIMEP

  • We need to evaluate the optimal interval for treating habitats with either

    • Larvicides (e.g., BTI)

    • Pupicides (e.g, Novalarone)

  • We need to evaluate the size of a buffer area around aquatic habitats to treat

  • We need to evaluate the effectiveness of these strategies in combination with

    • IRS

    • Auto-disseminated Larvicides.

To do this project, we will need to use MicroMoB. The current module is the Beverton Holt Model.

stage4L

We use this general notation:

  • \(\mu_i\) is fraction surviving

  • \(\theta_i\) is fraction maturing

\[ \begin{array}{rl} L_{1,t+1} &= \eta_t + \mu_1 (1-\theta_1) L_{1,t} \\ L_{2,t+1} & = \mu_1 \theta_1 L_{1,t} + \mu_2(1-\theta_2) L_{2,t} \\ L_{3,t+1} & = \mu_2 \theta_2 L_{2,t} + \mu_3(1-\theta_3) L_{3,t} \\ L_{4,t+1} & = \mu_3 \theta_3 L_{3,t} + \mu_4(1-\theta_4) L_{4,t} \\ P_{t+1} & = \mu_4 \theta_4 L_{4,t} + \mu_P(1-\theta_P) P_t \\ \Lambda_t &= \mu_P \theta_P P_t \end{array} \] The minimum time to go from egg to adult is 5 days.

stage6L

  • In this model, \(L_1\) and \(L_2\) are first instars:
  • In this model, \(L_3\) and \(L_4\) are second instars:

\[ \begin{array}{rl} L_{1,t+1} &= \eta_t + \mu_1 (1-\theta_1) L_{1,t} \\ L_{2,t+1} & = \mu_1 \theta_1 L_{1,t} + \mu_2(1-\theta_2) L_{2,t} \\ L_{3,t+1} & = \mu_2 \theta_2 L_{2,t} + \mu_3(1-\theta_3) L_{3,t} \\ L_{4,t+1} & = \mu_3 \theta_3 L_{3,t} + \mu_4(1-\theta_4) L_{4,t} \\ L_{5,t+1} & = \mu_4 \theta_4 L_{4,t} + \mu_5(1-\theta_5) L_{5,t} \\ L_{6,t+1} & = \mu_5 \theta_5 L_{5,t} + \mu_6(1-\theta_6) L_{6,t} \\ P_{t+1} & = \mu_6 \theta_6 L_{6,t} + \mu_P(1-\theta_P) P_t \\ \Lambda_t &= \mu_P \theta_P P_t \end{array} \]

The minimum time to go from egg to adult is 7 days.

  • In this model, \(L_1\) and \(L_2\) are first instars:
  • In this model, \(L_3\) and \(L_4\) are second instars:
  • In this model, \(L_5\) and \(L_6\) are third instars:
  • In this model, \(L_7\) and \(L_7\) are fourth instars:

\[ \begin{array}{rl} G_{t+1} &= \nu M_t \\ L_{1,t+1} &= \eta_t + \mu_1 (1-\theta_1) L_{1,t} \\ L_{2,t+1} & = \mu_1 \theta_1 L_{1,t} + \mu_2(1-\theta_2) L_{2,t} \\ L_{3,t+1} & = \mu_2 \theta_2 L_{2,t} + \mu_3(1-\theta_3) L_{3,t} \\ L_{4,t+1} & = \mu_3 \theta_3 L_{3,t} + \mu_4(1-\theta_4) L_{4,t} \\ L_{5,t+1} & = \mu_4 \theta_4 L_{4,t} + \mu_5(1-\theta_5) L_{5,t} \\ L_{6,t+1} & = \mu_5 \theta_5 L_{5,t} + \mu_6(1-\theta_6) L_{6,t} \\ L_{7,t+1} & = \mu_6 \theta_6 L_{6,t} + \mu_7(1-\theta_7) L_{7,t} \\ L_{8,t+1} & = \mu_7 \theta_7 L_{7,t} + \mu_8(1-\theta_8) L_{8,t} \\ P_{t+1} & = \mu_8 \theta_8 L_{8,t} + \mu_P(1-\theta_P) P_t \\ \Lambda_t &= \mu_P \theta_P P_t \\ M_{t+1} &= \Lambda_{t} + p M_t \end{array} \] The minimum time to go from egg to adult is 9 days.

Code

Here, we implement a generalized \(N-\)stage model

dL = function(vars, params){with(c(vars,params),{
  totL  = sum(L)
  dose  = ifelse(t%%re_treat == 0, 1, 0)*bti_dose
  mu    = mu0*exp(-muD*totL)*exp(-bti*bti_mu)
  theta = theta0*exp(-thetaD*totL)
 
  
  bti = bti_dk*bti + dose
  L = mu*L 
  Lt = (1-theta)*L 
  Lt[-1] = Lt[-1] + theta[-N]*L[-N]
  Lt[1] =  Lt[1] + params$eggs*M
  Pt = theta[N]*L[N]
  Lambdat = P
  Mt = Lambda + .95*M
  vars = list(t=t+1, bti=bti, L = Lt, P = Pt, Lambda=Lambdat, M=Mt)
  return(vars)
})}
sdL = function(vars, params){with(c(vars, params),{
  totL  = sum(L)
  dose  = ifelse(t%%re_treat == 0, 1, 0)*bti_dose
  mu    = mu0*exp(-muD*totL)*exp(-bti*bti_mu)
  theta = theta0*exp(-thetaD*totL)
  
  bti = bti_dk*bti + dose
  survive = rbinom(N, L, mu) 
  mature = rbinom(N, survive, theta) 
  Lt = survive-mature 
  Lt[-1] = Lt[-1] + mature[-N] 
  Pt = mature[N] 
  Lt[1] =  Lt[1] + rpois(1,params$eggs*M) 
  Lambdat = P
  Mt = Lambda + rbinom(1, M, .95)
  vars = list(t=t+1, bti=bti, L = Lt, P = Pt, Lambda=Lambdat, M=Mt)
  return(vars)
})}
makePars = function(N=8){
  mu0 = .99*rep(1,8) 
  theta0 = .99*rep(1,8) 
  muD = .00001
  thetaD = .00001
  params = list(N=8, mu0=mu0, muD=muD, theta0=theta0, thetaD=thetaD, re_treat = 15, bti_dk = .9, bti_mu = .2, bti_dose=2, eggs=200)
  return(params) 
} 
params = makePars()
L = rep(0,8)
P = 0 
P = 0 
vars = V0 =  list(t=0, bti=0, L=L, P=P, Lambda=0, M=10) 
#dL(vars, params) 
dL_iterate = function(vars, params, maxT=200, after=1, mtl=NULL){
  vars = V0
  V = unlist(vars)
  for(i in 1:maxT){
    dL(vars, params) -> vars
    V = rbind(V, unlist(vars)) 
  }
  if(after < maxT) plot(V[after:maxT,12], type = "l", ylab = expression(Lambda), main = mtl)
  return(V)
}
dL_iterate(vars, params) -> V1

sdL_iterate = function(vars, params, maxT=200, after=1, mtl=NULL){
  vars = V0
  V = unlist(vars)
  for(i in 1:maxT){
    sdL(vars, params) -> vars
    V = rbind(V, unlist(vars)) 
  }
  if(after < maxT) plot(V[after:maxT,12], type = "l", ylab = expression(Lambda), main = mtl)
  return(V)
}
sdL_iterate(vars, params)-> V2
